class Solution {
    public int countOperations(int num1, int num2) {
        int a = Math.max(num1, num2);
        int b = Math.min(num1, num2);
        int count = 0;
        while (b != 0) {
            count++;
            int temp = a / b;
            a = b;
            b = a % b;
            // equivalent to 
            // int temp = a;
            // a = b;
            // b = temp % b;
        }
        return count;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log min(num1, num2))
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution uses the mathematical property that the number of operations required to make either num1 = 0 or num2 = 0 is equivalent to the number of steps in the Euclidean algorithm to find the GCD of num1 and num2. This approach optimizes the process by directly computing the number of operations without simulating each step.

